div.p:
Infantry, eleven new regiments (eight Prussian, one
                        Bavarian, two Saxon), and one additional battalion will be added to the
                        regiment of the Grand Duchy of Hesse;

The German army will thus be strengthened by about 30,000 men and 300 guns;
                        and the number of men under arms during peace will, in future, be about
                        427,270.
